<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbfee2850-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s15964"><num value="15964">§ 15964.</num><heading> Clean coal centers of excellence</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbfee2851-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s15964/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As part of the clean coal power initiative, the Secretary shall award competitive, merit-based grants to institutions of higher education for the establishment of centers of excellence for energy systems of the future.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbfee2852-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s15964/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Basis for grants</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall award grants under this section to institutions of higher education that show the greatest potential for advancing new clean coal technologies.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idbfee2853-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tIV/s404">Pub. L. 109–58, title IV, § 404</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/753">119 Stat. 753</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
